1. Install Ubuntu with cdt as user

2. Login as cdt and download install script

	wget http://www.buch-kromann.dk/cdt/install.sh

3. Execute install script

	sh install.sh

4. Follow instructions in install script

5. Make boot floppy if necessary


BACKING UP DRIVE


6. Copy file system to harddisk with rsync


RESTORING COPY ON NEW DRIVE

7. Create ext3 and swap partitions on target drive

9. Copy file system back to harddisk with rsync

10. Set volume ids for / and swap
